  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with newly diagnosed lung cancer may have hypofunction of the adrenal cortex either
      from tumour metastasis or other mechanisms. Since lung cancer patient may have to undergo
      stressful investigation and treatments, undetected hypofunction of the adrenal cortex may be
      hazardous. Knowledge of the size of the problem may help determine whether routine check is
      warranted.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
